e-building projects. Indeed, these projects have thrust together an unlikely gathering of guerilla groups, drug-trafficking paramilitaries, military strategists, technocratic planners, local politicians, and development experts in an attempt to give concrete coherence to the inherently unwieldy abstraction of "the state" in a space in which it supposedly does not exist. By untangling this odd mix, Ballvé reveals how Colombia's violent conflicts have produced surprisingly coherent and resilient, if not at all benevolent, regimes of rule.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aColombiaxPolitics and governmenty1974- 0aParamilitary forceszColombiazUrabá. 0aParamilitary forceszColombiazUrabá. 0aPolitical violencezColombiazUrabá. 0aPolitical violencezColombiazUrabá. 4aAnthropology. 4aGeography-Physical & Cultural. 4aLatino/A Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aColombia, Territory, Paramilitaries, Civil war, political agency.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501747564zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501747564423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501747564/original  a978-3-11-069046-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-0704